HEADWORD: Keramographic
<hw>Ker`a*mo*graph"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ke`ramos</grk> tile + <ets>graph</ets> + <ets>ic</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Suitable to be written upon; capable of being written upon, as a
slate; -- said especially of a certain kind of globe.</def>
<rj><au>Scudamore.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

